21/12/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer and leading representatives of the business community discussed political and economic issues, during a meeting at the Turkish Industrialists' and Businessmen's Association on Tuesday (20 December). A key topic on the agenda was electoral reform, particularly lowering the present 10 per cent election threshold to 7 per cent or 8 per cent. (NTV, TurkishPress.com - 20/12/05)
